      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/returning-ground-webs-clouds" title="Returning to Ground from the Web&#039;s Clouds">Returning to Ground from the Web&#039;s Clouds</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/doc-searls" title="View user profile.">Doc Searls</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Jan 03, 2014 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_276 first active"><a href="/tag/cloud" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Cloud</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_351 last"><a href="/tag/freedom" rel="tag" title="">Freedom</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/returning-ground-webs-clouds" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
The Net as we know it today first became visible to me in March 1994, when
I was among several hundred other tech types gathered at Esther Dyson's PC
Forum conference in Arizona.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/returning-ground-webs-clouds"> more>></a></span></p>
