 <a href="/content/introduction-openstack" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/OpenStack (1).png" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/introduction-openstack" title="Introduction to OpenStack">Introduction to OpenStack</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/tom-fifield" title="View user profile.">Tom Fifield</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Oct 10, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_276 first active"><a href="/tag/cloud" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Cloud</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_899 last"><a href="/tag/openstack" rel="tag" title="">OpenStack</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/introduction-openstack" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

What is OpenStack? 
<p>You've probably heard of OpenStack. It's that cloud software that's getting a lot of attention
 from big names in the IT industry and major users like CERN, Comcast and PayPal. However, 
 did you know that it's more than that? It's also the fastest growing open source community 
 in the world, and a very interesting collaboration among technology vendors and users.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/introduction-openstack"> more>></a></span></p>

  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/introduction-openstack#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">3 comments</a></li>
</ul>
